# Backend request UX

## Rule 1 — Loading data

When displaying data from the API:

- Show `LoadingState` (or inline `SpinnerIcon`) while the request is in flight.
- Do **not** show empty-state text (`No flights yet`, `No data yet`, `Flight not found`, etc.) until the request has **completed** (`initialized` / `listInitialized` / `detailInitialized` is `true`).
- Use composable flags:
  - `loading` — read/fetch in progress
  - `initialized` — first fetch finished (success or error)

```vue
<LoadingState v-if="!initialized && loading" />
<ErrorBanner v-else-if="error" :retry-busy="loading" @retry="fetch" />
<div v-else-if="initialized && !items.length">No items yet.</div>
```

## Rule 2 — User actions

When a click triggers a backend request:

- Disable the clicked control until response **or timeout** (30s via `apiFetch`).
- Show spinner on that control (`ActionButton` with `:busy`, or `ConfirmDialog` `:busy`).
- Prevent duplicate submissions (`if (mutating.value) return` at start of handler).
- Use `mutating` in composables for writes (create/update/delete/save/connect/logout) — separate from read `loading`.

```vue
<ActionButton :busy="mutating" @click="save">Save</ActionButton>
```

## Shared components

| Component | Use |
|-----------|-----|
| `SpinnerIcon` | Inline spinner |
| `LoadingState` | Full-section data loading |
| `ActionButton` | Buttons with `:busy` + auto-disable |
| `ConfirmDialog` | `:busy` on confirm during delete |
| `ErrorBanner` | `:retry-busy` on Retry button |
